WEBVTT

00:02.090 --> 00:03.799
Previously on Dexter.

00:03.925 --> 00:06.301
We must catch them at the shipyard.

00:06.428 --> 00:09.930
He's gonna find out
and then he's gonna kill me.

00:10.932 --> 00:13.225
Harry knew my mother.

00:13.351 --> 00:17.021
Why would Rita have Narcotics Anonymous
literature if Paul's dead?

00:17.147 --> 00:20.357
Because recently l entered the program.

00:20.483 --> 00:23.110
How many fucking ways
do l have to tell you l'm fine?

00:23.236 --> 00:27.156
This is my department. l need to know
you're fit for duty. That's my job.

00:27.282 --> 00:30.701
l always eat lunch at one o'clock.
You'll learn that about me.

00:30.827 --> 00:32.786
Sit down.

00:32.912 --> 00:35.664
You're very fidgety.
Anyone ever tell you that?

00:35.790 --> 00:39.168
My father. You applying for the job?

00:39.294 --> 00:43.047
But you said you'd call. Where are you
and when are you coming back?

00:43.757 --> 00:47.509
- Tomorrow morning.
- Promise you'll stop by the house?

00:47.635 --> 00:49.887
- l'll see you soon.
- ls she cool with this?

00:50.013 --> 00:52.181
- l didn't tell her.
- l don't care what you did.

00:52.307 --> 00:54.391
I'm not sure who made me what I am.

00:54.517 --> 00:56.810
Thing is, l've met someone
who doesn't care.

00:56.936 --> 00:59.021
l want to talk to you about Coral Cove.

00:59.147 --> 01:02.483
- What about it?
- The algae on the rocks sent us there.

01:02.609 --> 01:06.528
l'd seriously consider moving your boat.
Security out there sucks ass.

01:06.654 --> 01:10.324
When l get back, l need to make sure there's
no blood traces on my boat.

01:10.450 --> 01:14.369
This isn't a commerciaI marina
but l see the upkeep is dismal,

01:14.496 --> 01:17.873
so l'm ordering 24-hour surveillance
on this marina and the others.

03:17.285 --> 03:21.288
There's another shipment
coming in tomorrow. Cocaine.

03:23.458 --> 03:26.168
- How much?
- 300 bricks, give or take.

03:29.005 --> 03:33.425
- Can you get your hands on some?
- That wasn't part of our agreement.

03:33.551 --> 03:39.473
Look, we need hard evidence, otherwise
it's just your word against Estrada's.

03:39.599 --> 03:43.101
l'll protect you. l promise.

03:47.815 --> 03:49.858
You better.

03:51.361 --> 03:53.445
Would you meet me later?

03:53.988 --> 03:56.156
Laura, the tape's still rolling.

04:04.832 --> 04:06.667
Very convincing.

04:08.378 --> 04:10.462
What was that?

04:16.427 --> 04:18.512
Laura, the tape's still rolling.

04:21.266 --> 04:23.058
Damn it.

04:23.184 --> 04:27.062
My mother,
confidentiaI informant and mumbIer.

04:29.357 --> 04:32.734
Whatever she had to whisper,
l probably don"t want to hear.

04:35.738 --> 04:40.075
lt seems that my foster father and
my biological mother were having an affair.

04:40.201 --> 04:44.162
lt's bad enough l can't shake the visual
but the questions...

04:44.289 --> 04:47.791
Did he bIame himseIf for her death?
ls that why he took me in?

04:48.251 --> 04:51.044
Did he love her or was he just using her?

04:52.046 --> 04:53.880
Was he using me?

04:54.465 --> 04:58.427
l thought Harry's code was on-the-spot
creative problem solving

04:58.553 --> 05:01.722
but maybe he planned for me
to settle the score all along.

05:04.350 --> 05:07.269
It's times Iike this I wish
l really were a drug addict.

05:07.395 --> 05:10.188
l had problems as a kid
because of what happened to my mother.

05:10.315 --> 05:13.483
Harry said he'd help me
but we only talked about his rules.

05:13.609 --> 05:16.695
l spent so much time trying
to live up to his expectations

05:16.821 --> 05:19.239
because l thought he had
my interests in mind but. . .

05:19.365 --> 05:23.660
lf you come over this late,
at least you could bring me a coffee.

05:23.786 --> 05:27.372
- sorry.
- Cappuccino. Make a note of it.

05:34.339 --> 05:38.175
Truth is, Dex, doesn't really matter
why Harry did what he did.

05:38.301 --> 05:41.636
The result's the same.
You have an addiction.

05:43.598 --> 05:45.932
Do you think Harry made me what l am?

05:46.517 --> 05:50.687
Plenty of people go through trauma
without turning to addiction.

05:50.813 --> 05:54.483
Whatever Harry taught you
led you down the wrong path.

05:55.360 --> 05:59.571
But l built everything in my life
on what Harry said l was supposed to be.

05:59.697 --> 06:01.698
My job, girlfriend. . .

06:03.034 --> 06:05.577
lt's all what Harry told me l needed.

06:06.287 --> 06:08.121
What do you think you need?

06:11.125 --> 06:12.709
l have no idea.

06:12.835 --> 06:17.589
Whatever's inside you is splattered
all over that paper that l took from your lab.

06:19.133 --> 06:21.134
Looks messy.

06:21.260 --> 06:23.845
lt probably is.

06:23.971 --> 06:25.847
Look, Dexter,

06:27.308 --> 06:29.351
everyone has a moment when they realize

06:29.477 --> 06:33.355
that their value system
is different from their parents'.

06:33.481 --> 06:37.484
Mine was in college, but, hey,
maybe you're a late bloomer.

06:37.610 --> 06:40.362
- Lucky me.
- Damn right, lucky you.

06:41.155 --> 06:43.490
You get to have a fresh start.

06:43.616 --> 06:46.827
Whatever you thought,
whatever you did doesn't matter.

06:47.453 --> 06:50.038
Now you get to figure out who you are.

06:55.378 --> 06:59.339
l went to Lila for answers
but now all l have is more questions.

06:59.465 --> 07:01.716
Who am I? What do I need?

07:01.843 --> 07:03.927
What do I want?

07:04.053 --> 07:06.555
Coffee. l really want a cup of coffee.

07:06.681 --> 07:09.224
- What up, half-day?
- ls there coffee left?

07:09.350 --> 07:12.477
- You're late.
- l fell asleep before you got home.

07:12.603 --> 07:14.688
Were you at Rita's?

07:16.732 --> 07:18.859
You're welcome, ass.

07:18.985 --> 07:21.903
- Your brother looks like shit.
- Tell me about it.

07:22.029 --> 07:25.907
l may be out of line with this
but did he fall off the wagon?

07:26.534 --> 07:30.871
What wagon? The only wagon
Dexter's ever had is a Radio Flyer.

07:30.997 --> 07:33.123
Your brother's a junkie.

07:33.875 --> 07:36.042
- lsn't he?
- Dexter?

07:37.378 --> 07:40.505
Are you high? He's never even
smoked a cigarette.

07:41.632 --> 07:47.012
l'm glad you got some new material, though,
'cause "freak" and "psycho" were getting tired.

08:00.193 --> 08:02.068
Agent Lundy.

08:02.487 --> 08:06.114
So, l hear a rumor you're tracking
all our internet activity.

08:06.240 --> 08:08.074
So is it true?

08:08.201 --> 08:10.827
'Cause l can explain all that she-male stuff.

08:12.747 --> 08:16.791
- l need my team outside in five minutes.
- That sounds important.

08:16.918 --> 08:21.546
Got a major break. Patrol found a guy
saying he escaped the Bay Harbor Butcher.

08:21.672 --> 08:24.466
He claimed he was captured
a couple hours ago.

08:24.592 --> 08:28.929
Well, that"s a neat trick, considering
l was asleep. At least trying to sleep.

08:29.055 --> 08:31.139
- Could be good news for me.
- Morgan.

08:31.265 --> 08:33.266
- Yes.
- The other Morgan.

08:34.101 --> 08:36.478
l'd like you to join us if you can spare him.

08:36.604 --> 08:38.647
That's fine with me.

08:38.773 --> 08:40.941
- ls there blood?
- Not that l'm aware of.

08:41.067 --> 08:45.487
- But what about Masuka?
- Yeah, l'm the lead forensics investigator.

08:45.613 --> 08:49.407
Masuka's lab work is pressing.
l need him to hold down the fort here.

08:49.534 --> 08:51.910
He totally saw the she-male stuff.

08:52.036 --> 08:54.913
So, what do you say? l'll buy you lunch after.

08:55.039 --> 08:58.917
- Pork sandwich, right?
- Yes. sure.

08:59.043 --> 09:03.338
Good. l figured it was time to get
a fresh perspective on the case.

09:03.464 --> 09:07.259
Rumor has it you have a knack
for attracting serial killers.

09:07.385 --> 09:11.012
- l hear the same about you.
- Dexter also enjoys walks on the beach

09:11.138 --> 09:15.100
- and foreign films.
- Then we've got a lot to talk about.

09:38.165 --> 09:41.126
He knocked me out.
Then, when l woke up,

09:41.252 --> 09:43.628
l was tied up in that train car over there.

09:43.754 --> 09:46.298
- You said he used rope?
- Dumb fuck.

09:47.383 --> 09:50.927
l stretched it out so l can get my legs free
and then busted out.

09:51.053 --> 09:53.722
Ran across the road.
almost got hit by that guy's car.

09:53.848 --> 09:57.017
So that's the alleged victim
of the Bay Harbor Butcher.

09:58.644 --> 10:00.729
But I've never seen him before.

10:00.855 --> 10:02.897
Dex!

10:03.024 --> 10:06.985
O'Connor, Singer. Make sure
you take pictures of those footprints.

10:07.111 --> 10:08.570
- Hey, Dex.
- Hey.

10:08.696 --> 10:12.240
So the victim says the Butcher
held him in this train car.

10:12.366 --> 10:16.161
Lundy wants a search for trace evidence.
Your spidey sense tingling?

10:16.287 --> 10:19.164
- We'll see when l get inside.
- Take your time.

10:19.290 --> 10:22.083
We've never been this close to this pendejo.

10:22.209 --> 10:24.336
Closer than you think, amigo.

10:36.223 --> 10:38.099
He may have borrowed my pseudonym

10:38.225 --> 10:42.062
but this guy doesn't know
the first thing about my techniques.

10:42.188 --> 10:44.022
Amateur.

10:44.148 --> 10:45.774
What makes you think it was the Butcher?

10:45.900 --> 10:49.778
He said the Bay Harbor Butcher's
gonna clean up Miami.

10:49.904 --> 10:52.197
He said, "You're gonna get
what you deserve."

10:52.323 --> 10:54.449
And what do you deserve, Mr. Henry?

10:54.575 --> 10:58.078
Well, look, the butcher kills criminals, right?

10:58.871 --> 11:00.538
l just got out of jail, you know?

11:00.665 --> 11:04.250
Six years for aggravated assault
and home invasion. so...

11:04.377 --> 11:08.088
He kills murderers.
You didn't kill anyone, did you?

11:08.214 --> 11:11.091
All right, l gave this old guy a heart attack.

11:12.259 --> 11:14.469
lt's not like l was doing it on purpose.

11:14.595 --> 11:17.806
l used to hit. you know.
retirement homes, communities.

11:17.932 --> 11:20.600
Snowbirds are easy targets.

11:20.726 --> 11:23.978
And l don't do that any more. l did my time.

11:24.105 --> 11:26.356
Your mother must be so proud.

11:28.275 --> 11:31.236
l want to check out
the train car with your brother.

11:32.196 --> 11:36.491
Why don't you, er, keep an eye on our friend
here while we confirm his story?

11:37.326 --> 11:40.161
Oh, yeah. Sure.

11:42.957 --> 11:46.167
Killing tools left behind.
I'd never be this careIess.

11:46.293 --> 11:49.295
whoever did this would
never pass Harry's muster.

11:50.464 --> 11:52.340
Then again, neither would Harry.

11:52.466 --> 11:57.595
He lied about my past. He cheated on my
foster mother with my biological mother.

11:58.222 --> 12:01.182
Maybe Lila"s right. lt"s time
for a new set of standards.

12:01.308 --> 12:05.603
lf you were the Bay Harbor Butcher,
would you use a place like this?

12:07.815 --> 12:12.569
Actually, yes. Locationwise,
it's not a bad choice.

12:12.695 --> 12:15.488
lt's quiet, remote.

12:16.782 --> 12:20.452
Could use an upgrade
in the lighting department, but. . .

12:24.206 --> 12:26.291
So you think this is our guy?

12:27.543 --> 12:29.753
Not exactly.

12:30.921 --> 12:34.632
From what l understand, this space
doesn't support his MO.

12:34.759 --> 12:36.718
lt's filthy, for one thing.

12:39.346 --> 12:42.557
Butcher's clean, orderly. . .

12:48.522 --> 12:50.982
. . .and some people would say compulsive.

12:54.445 --> 12:58.448
- Really? You think he's compulsive?
- This doesn't fit. either.

12:58.574 --> 13:00.450
A hatchet is sloppy.

13:01.535 --> 13:04.412
The butcher uses precise
surgical instruments.

13:04.955 --> 13:10.460
Well. he's not that predictable. is he?
He mixes it up, different tools every time.

13:10.586 --> 13:12.420
And never rope.

13:12.546 --> 13:14.964
He uses duct tape and plastic wrap.

13:15.090 --> 13:19.010
- Plastic wrap? How can you tell?
- Depression patterns in the skin.

13:20.805 --> 13:23.723
Maybe the butcher's
having an identity crisis.

13:25.226 --> 13:28.019
- lt's entirely possible.
- But not likely.

13:29.188 --> 13:34.234
My guess is we're looking for a vigilante
inspired by the butcher's principles.

13:34.360 --> 13:36.653
Bet he never thought he'd be a role model.

13:36.779 --> 13:38.655
l bet you're right.

13:40.241 --> 13:43.493
So, any new leads on the real guy?

13:43.619 --> 13:47.413
Not yet. We're hoping the cameras'll
turn something up.

13:47.998 --> 13:49.749
- Cameras?
- ln the marinas.

13:49.875 --> 13:54.254
Put them in a couple of days ago
to monitor for suspicious activities.

13:54.839 --> 13:58.049
Good news for all those cops
who keep boats at Coral Cove.

13:58.175 --> 14:00.343
You've got one, too, right?

14:04.098 --> 14:08.226
Yeah. Yeah. we've been needing
a security upgrade for a long time now.

14:10.980 --> 14:12.605
Has Lundy seen me on the tape?

14:12.731 --> 14:15.775
ls that why he invited me along today,
to mess with me?

14:21.282 --> 14:27.161
Hey. l'm sorry if l was short with you this
morning. l'm lost without my morning coffee.

14:27.288 --> 14:29.497
Whatever.

14:29.623 --> 14:32.500
How was your play date with Lundy?
Did you bond?

14:33.419 --> 14:36.588
You didn't say they put up
security cameras at the marinas.

14:36.714 --> 14:40.842
They're not doing any good. We have
to update the station's computer system

14:40.968 --> 14:43.094
before we can synch
with Lundy's equipment.

14:43.220 --> 14:47.557
- so the cameras aren't recording?
- They are but nobody's seen the footage.

14:47.683 --> 14:51.811
- Lundy said it should be fixed by tonight.
- Well, that's a relief.

15:02.781 --> 15:05.658
Your mom told me about
your cultural presentation.

15:05.784 --> 15:08.161
Did your teacher assign you a country yet?

15:09.455 --> 15:11.331
Saudi Arabia.

15:11.832 --> 15:13.791
No. That's lsrael.

15:14.335 --> 15:18.463
- l won't tell the Saudis you said that.
- Cody's enjoying himself.

15:18.589 --> 15:22.342
- Dexter's very patient with him.
- Dexter's a saint.

15:23.552 --> 15:26.512
- Where's Astor?
- She's by the water.

15:28.015 --> 15:29.724
l want to say goodbye.

15:29.850 --> 15:33.519
l got to go. l was supposed
to meet Lila ten minutes ago.

15:35.731 --> 15:38.900
- Who's Lila?
- His sponsor.

15:39.026 --> 15:41.069
Really? A woman?

15:41.779 --> 15:46.324
Yes, Mom. Dexter's sponsor is a woman.
ls that a problem?

15:47.409 --> 15:49.494
ls she attractive?

15:49.620 --> 15:52.080
- Look. Mom...
- l'm just curious.

15:52.998 --> 15:54.958
ls she?

15:55.709 --> 15:59.337
l have an idea. Why don't you and Lila
have dinner with us?

16:00.631 --> 16:03.091
That's very kind of you, Gail, but, erm. . .

16:03.217 --> 16:07.053
lt would be nice if we got to know the woman
you're spending so much time with.

16:07.179 --> 16:10.723
- Mom, they're doing step work.
- But they have to eat, right?

16:17.147 --> 16:19.732
- Oh, here. Let me help.
- Thank you.

16:24.071 --> 16:26.155
So lovely of you to have me over.

16:27.741 --> 16:29.909
Now l can put names to faces.

16:30.035 --> 16:32.412
Dexter talks about you all the time.

16:33.247 --> 16:35.081
Good things, l hope.

16:36.083 --> 16:38.668
Dexter never says a bad word
about anyone.

16:49.722 --> 16:54.017
Tell me, Lila. What exactly
are you recovering from?

16:55.269 --> 16:57.270
l'm a meth addict.

16:57.396 --> 16:59.355
Sober five years.

16:59.481 --> 17:03.151
l don't know much about meth.
Rita's ex-husband shot heroin.

17:03.277 --> 17:05.653
Like Dexter.

17:05.779 --> 17:07.864
Guess we know your type, don't we?

17:08.782 --> 17:10.742
Just can't seem to help myself.

17:13.454 --> 17:15.246
You have nothing to worry about.

17:15.372 --> 17:17.874
With Dexter, l mean.

17:19.043 --> 17:20.752
l'm sitting right here.

17:20.878 --> 17:24.505
- l didn't mean to imply. . .
- No. l completely understand.

17:24.631 --> 17:28.760
Rita's your little baby.
You have every right to be concerned.

17:28.886 --> 17:32.638
But if l can reassure you,
Dexter's doing incredibly well.

17:34.683 --> 17:36.934
Well, l'm happy to hear that.

17:37.061 --> 17:39.562
l'm sure it has everything to do with you two.

17:39.688 --> 17:42.482
From what he tells me,
you're very supportive.

17:42.608 --> 17:44.650
Dexter's lucky to have you.

17:45.360 --> 17:47.361
That's very sweet of you to say.

17:48.280 --> 17:53.701
So, Lila, tell us more about yourself.
Dexter tells me you're an artist.

17:53.827 --> 17:58.122
Yeah, she does amazing things
with a blowtorch. What's it called?

17:58.957 --> 18:00.833
Talent?

18:03.045 --> 18:07.381
But l'm not the only artist
at the table.

18:09.510 --> 18:12.470
Dexter? Since when?

18:12.596 --> 18:17.100
lt's not really art. She's talking
about a blood-spatter pattern from work.

18:17.226 --> 18:20.394
What kind of career choice
is blood spatter. exactly?

18:22.523 --> 18:24.607
He helps catch criminals, Mother.

18:25.776 --> 18:31.030
And it makes perfect sense, really.
What with Dexter's mother and everything.

18:33.367 --> 18:35.034
You know.

18:35.160 --> 18:37.370
She's. . .dead.

18:43.377 --> 18:45.211
Forgot the bread.

18:47.172 --> 18:51.134
Dinner was fantastic, Rita.
And this dessert. Wow.

18:56.515 --> 18:59.600
l never thought l'd say this
but l kind of like her.

19:00.644 --> 19:03.062
Yeah, me too. She's really helping me.

19:05.607 --> 19:08.317
l wish she didn't have to help you tonight.

19:09.361 --> 19:13.114
- Why? What are you thinking?
- Mm. My mom could watch the kids.

19:13.240 --> 19:15.408
l have to swing by the office tonight.

19:16.451 --> 19:19.370
l need to take care
of something really important.

19:19.997 --> 19:22.790
Oh, honey, can't it wait till morning?

19:22.916 --> 19:24.959
l promise we'll go straight to bed.

19:25.085 --> 19:29.005
You're very convincing
but it needs to get done tonight.

19:30.465 --> 19:32.466
Just give me an hour, OK?

19:33.093 --> 19:35.386
- Meet you back at my place?
- OK.

19:42.561 --> 19:45.104
l think it's funny you write children's books.

19:45.230 --> 19:50.067
Yeah. a big. tough guy like me should do
something manly, huh, like wrangling cattle?

19:50.194 --> 19:54.405
l don't even know any kids' books.
My dad told me cop stories before bed.

19:55.782 --> 19:59.118
lt was really the only alone time
l ever got with him.

20:01.622 --> 20:03.915
- You OK?
- Yeah.

20:05.667 --> 20:08.461
Sorry. Just an annoying day at work.

20:12.758 --> 20:15.676
You know that FBl guy l was talking about?

20:15.802 --> 20:19.347
l was really starting to feel
like l was his go-to girl but. . .

20:20.724 --> 20:24.185
- He realized Dexter is the superior Morgan.
- That's not true.

20:24.311 --> 20:27.605
l should be used to it.
lt was like that with my dad, work.

20:28.982 --> 20:31.692
- l hoped with Lundy it would be different.
- Why?

20:31.818 --> 20:34.320
l don't know.

20:35.322 --> 20:37.323
l respect him.

20:37.991 --> 20:40.368
He's great at his job,

20:40.494 --> 20:42.453
super smart,

20:43.622 --> 20:47.792
and funny but in this really dry way
where he doesn't even know it.

20:48.585 --> 20:50.628
You love him.

20:51.171 --> 20:53.172
What?

20:53.298 --> 20:56.050
- No.
- You do. You have a crush on Grundy.

20:56.176 --> 20:58.594
- Lundy.
- Oh, now you're touchy about it.

20:58.720 --> 21:03.349
l don't have a crush on him. He's like
my dad. except l spent my whole life

21:03.475 --> 21:08.020
trying to get my dad to notice me and he
actually pays attention to what l have to say.

21:08.146 --> 21:12.358
- And Grundy loves you.
- Oh. fuck off.

21:30.627 --> 21:32.670
Lundy's good. Double locked.

21:34.047 --> 21:36.090
And a bit beyond my expertise.

21:36.800 --> 21:40.052
l could try to crack it open
but in my own station...

21:41.221 --> 21:43.055
Too risky.

21:53.191 --> 21:56.068
l can do this more often
now that my mom's in town.

21:58.322 --> 22:00.406
l feel like we're being bad.

22:04.077 --> 22:06.495
Bad? Bad is good.

22:08.081 --> 22:09.874
Oh, let the machine get it.

22:11.835 --> 22:14.003
Hey, Dex, just calling to check in.

22:14.129 --> 22:18.257
To have a debriefing on dinner.
l thought it went well, don't you?

22:18.383 --> 22:23.262
- l'd say so.
- Rita's sweet. Very Martha Stewart.

22:24.222 --> 22:26.307
l love Martha Stewart.

22:26.433 --> 22:30.144
God, her mum. She"s got quite
the rod up her arse, doesn't she?

22:30.270 --> 22:34.482
